        <body>
            <pb n="1R"/>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <addressee>Rev Mr Isaac Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Since I am very busy to day I must<lb/> beg you to excuse me when I
                only acknowledge your<lb/> labour of last weeks, and assure you that it grieves
                me<lb/> to think that you will probably retire from public<lb/> business; every one
                laboring in the cause of Judaism may<lb/> say <add>מי יקום לי עם מרעים מי יתיצב לי
                    עם פעלי עון און</add>.</p>
            <p>Good news in <placeName>Albany</placeName>. My cause against <persName>Louis
                    Spanier</persName><lb/> was decided on <add>פרשת בהר שבת</add> before the
                Mayor's court<lb/> of this City. I have fought the battle of all ministers in<lb/>
                this country and the victory <del>of th</del> is ours.</p>
            <list type="ordered">
                <head>The decisions of the Judge are</head>
                <item n="1">A minister elected by the majority of the Congregation<lb/> can be
                    deposed only by a vote of said majority, otherwise<lb/> none dare prevent him or
                    interfere with him in the<lb/> discharge of his official duties.</item>
                <item n="2">All acts of a <add>פרנס</add>
                    <add>Parnass</add> without the consent of the majority<lb/> of trustees are
                    illegal</item>
                <item n="3">The meeting of the Congregation Beth-El on the <date>5. of<lb/>
                        September</date> last is illegal and all resolutions passed<lb/> are null
                    and void, because 1. No notice was given, that resolutions <del>shall</del> will
                    be <del>passed</del> offered regarding the minster<lb/> of the
                        Congregation<del>s</del>, and still such resolutions were<lb/> passed at
                    said meeting; 2 motions were made and<lb/> seconded to adjourn the meeting,
                    which the chair<lb/> refused to put to the meeting; in consequence of which the
                    majority of the trustees after a delay of two hours<lb/>
                    <sic>anounced</sic> the meeting adjourned, to which the majority<lb/> of the
                    congregation responded and left the meeting;<lb/> only 43 out of the 132 members
                    of the Congregation<lb/> remained and passed resolution concerning <persName
                        role="author">Dr. Wise</persName>,</item>
                <pb n="1V"/>
                <item n="4">The plaintiff <persName role="author">Isaac M. Wise</persName> DD. was
                    bound in duty<lb/> to mount the pulpit on <date>Sabbath</date> next,
                        <date>September 7</date>,<lb/> as he usually did, and did so in a legal and
                    orderly<lb/> manner.</item>
                <item n="5">The defendant<persName> Louis Spanier</persName> had no right to<lb/>
                    interfere nor to stand at the pulpit.</item>
                <item n="6">The <del>plain f</del> defendant prevented <del>prevented</del> the<lb/>
                    plaintiff from the discharge of his duty by inflicting<lb/> upon him blows and
                    pushes.</item>
                <item n="7">The defendant is guilty of an <sic>insault</sic> &amp; battery<lb/>
                    committed on a minister in the pulpit in the<lb/> presence of his
                    congregation.</item>
            </list>
            <p>The jury then retired and brought in a verdict<lb/> of thousand dollars and
                costs.</p>
            <p>I wish you publish these 7 points as the court decided,<lb/> that I be justified
                before the world; let the world<lb/> know, that not I but <persName>Louis
                    Spanier</persName> created a riot<lb/> in a Synagogue on the first day of
                    <add>ראש השנה</add>; let the<lb/> world also know, that a <add>פרנס</add> has no
                right to do<lb/> harm to a minister. I have been defiled before<lb/> the world and I
                do ask of you to restore me by<lb/> publishing these facts, as the court confirmed
                them.<lb/> I am responsible as to the truth of these facts; but<lb/> I do not wish
                to give my name as correspondent.</p>
            <p>My time forbids to write more.</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)"><sic>Truely</sic> yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(5)">
                <persName role="author">Dr Wise</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">
                <placeName>Albany</placeName>
                <date>May 18. 1851</date>
            </p>
